  "response": "Here are some key things NOT to do if you are a cash-rich, fast-growing startup:\n\n1. Avoid Unnecessary Spending\n- Don't waste money on lavish offices\n- Avoid unnecessary perks\n- Don't hire too many people too quickly\n- Don't spend excessively on marketing without clear ROI\n\n2. Financial Management Mistakes\n- Don't ignore financial discipline\n- Don't burn cash without a clear strategy\n- Avoid premature scaling\n- Don't neglect cash flow projections\n\n3. Strategic Errors\n- Don't lose focus on core business\n- Avoid diversifying too early\n- Don't overpay for acquisitions\n- Don't chase vanity metrics\n\n4. Team and Culture Pitfalls\n- Don't compromise on hiring quality\n- Avoid building a toxic work culture\n- Don't ignore employee retention\n- Don't create excessive hierarchy\n\n5. Investment and Funding Mistakes\n- Don't take funding without a clear plan\n- Avoid giving away too much equity\n- Don't raise money just because you can\n- Don't ignore investor alignment\n\n6. Product and Market Risks\n- Don't neglect product-market fit\n- Avoid overcomplicating your product\n- Don't ignore customer feedback\n- Don't stop innovating\n\n7. Governance and Compliance\n- Don't overlook legal and regulatory requirements\n- Avoid poor corporate governance\n- Don't ignore risk management\n- Don't compromise on transparency",
